with the committee.

16
00:01:36,863 --> 00:01:39,365
The cargo left from Sasebo Port yesterday,

17
00:01:39,366 --> 00:01:40,916
and is now making its way here
across the Pacific Ocean.

18
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:47,539
A MIG-55 D transport helicopter!

19
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:51,210
I'd never have had the chance to fly in one
if it weren't for something like this.

20
00:01:51,211 --> 00:01:54,491
Man, this is what friends are for, right, Shinji?

21
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:59,585
I figured you'd get claustrophobic looking at
the same mountains day after day,

22
00:01:59,586 --> 00:02:02,722
so I invited you on a date,
since it is a Sunday.

23
00:02:02,723 --> 00:02:06,892
What?! Then today is a real date?

24
00:02:06,893 --> 00:02:11,530
I bought this cap just for today, Miss Misato!

25
00:02:11,531 --> 00:02:13,432
So, where are we headed?

26
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:16,153
We're taking a little jaunt across the Pacific
on a gorgeous cruise ship.

27
00:02:19,373 --> 00:02:23,542
Wow! Five aircraft carriers and
four battleships! What a fleet!

28
00:02:23,543 --> 00:02:26,478
This really IS what friends are for!

29
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,614
That's your gorgeous cruise ship?

30
00:02:28,615 --> 00:02:29,948
Yeah, she sure is gorgeous!

31
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:32,118
That's the pride of the U.N.,
the glorious regular carrier

32
00:02:32,119 --> 00:02:34,019
"Over the Rainbow"!

33
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:35,421
It's huge.

34
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:38,557
I'm surprised that such a relic is still afloat.

35
00:02:38,558 --> 00:02:39,892
Nabh, it's not so bad.

36
00:02:39,893 --> 00:02:42,523
It's a vintage model from before
the Second Impact.

37
00:02:44,064 --> 00:02:46,698
Give me a break!

38
