101
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:08,968
Shit! Those kids are really going
to save the Earth?

102
00:06:08,969 --> 00:06:11,136
Times are changing.

103
00:06:11,137 --> 00:06:14,373
I understand that Congress has also
pinned its hopes on that robot.

104
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:17,977
On that toy? The idiots!

105
00:06:17,978 --> 00:06:21,078
If they've got the money for it,
they should give it to us!

106
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:29,054
What are you doing here?!

107
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,689
Accompanying her.

108
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:32,210
I'm on a business trip from Germany.

109
00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:37,296
Man, was I careless.
I should have anticipated this.

110
00:06:37,297 --> 00:06:39,164
Hey! Don't touch me!

111
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:40,399
I can't help it!

112
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:43,269
Squadron 3 will sortie as scheduled.

113
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:46,238
Seeing anyone right now?

114
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,641
And that would be your business WHY?

115
00:06:48,642 --> 00:06:50,892
What? You're kind of cold.

116
00:06:52,012 --> 00:06:54,580
I hear that you're living with Katsuragi?

117
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,415
Yes.

118
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:59,256
So, does she still toss and turn in bed?

119
00:07:02,489 --> 00:07:04,590
Wha... wha...

120
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,141
What are you saying?!

121
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:09,995
So, she hasn't changed, has she,
Mister Shinji lkari?

122
00:07:09,996 --> 00:07:11,563
Well...

123
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:14,033
Huh? How do you know my name?

124
00:07:14,034 --> 00:07:15,567
Well, of course I do.

125
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:18,370
You're famous in our business.

126
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:21,741
The Third Child, who piloted an Eva
in battle with no training.

127
00:07:22,943 --> 00:07:25,911
Oh, no, it was just luck.

128
00:07:25,912 --> 00:07:29,102
Luck is a part of your destiny. It's your talent.

129
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,817
Well, I'll see you later.

130
00:07:31,818 --> 00:07:32,284
See you.

131
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:33,925
This has got to be a bad joke.
No, a nightmare.

132
00:07:37,057 --> 00:07:39,224
So, what do you think about
Mister Shinji lkari?

133
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:44,029
He's boring. That's the great Third Child?
What a disappointment.

134
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:48,600
Yet his sync ratio was well over 40%
in combat with no training.

135
00:07:48,601 --> 00:07:50,169
No way!

136
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:53,038
That captain's attitude gets on my nerves.

137
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:55,140
He's a proud man.

138
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,810
Pride can make you sarcastic.

139
00:07:57,811 --> 00:08:01,013
That Mr. Kaji is pretty lively and funny.

140
00:08:01,014 --> 00:08:03,615
He hasn't changed at all, that jerk.

141
00:08:03,616 --> 00:08:04,876
Hey, Third Child!

142
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,579
Come with me!

143
00:08:15,862 --> 00:08:19,331
So Unit 02 is red? I didn't know that.

144
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:22,501
The color isn't the only difference.

145
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,636
After all, Units 00 and 01 were created

146
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:27,706
as part of a development process,
prototype and test type.

147
00:08:27,707 --> 00:08:32,707
The fact that it synchronized with an
untrained pilot like you is proof of that.

148
00:08:32,746 --> 00:08:35,180
But Unit 02 is different.

149
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:37,216
Created for actual combat conditions,

150
00:08:37,217 --> 00:08:40,519
this is the world's first true Evangelion.

151
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,809
This is the final model!

152
00:08:44,424 --> 00:08:45,824
What was that?

153
00:08:45,825 --> 00:08:48,494
An undersea shock wave!

154
00:08:48,495 --> 00:08:49,725
That explosion was nearby!

155
00:08:51,598 --> 00:08:52,588
What's that?

156
00:08:56,669 --> 00:08:58,237
Could it be an Angel?

157
00:08:58,238 --> 00:08:59,848
That? A real one?

158
00:09:02,008 --> 00:09:04,848
What'll we do? We have to get back
to Miss Misato.

159
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,630
This is my chance!

160
00:09:14,287 --> 00:09:17,589
All ships take evasive action,
but watch the formation!

161
00:09:17,590 --> 00:09:19,191
Where's the status report?

162
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:23,395
The Cymbeline's gone silent.
Titus Andronicus can't locate the target!

163
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:26,131
Damn it! What in the hell is going on here?!

164
00:09:26,132 --> 00:09:28,100
Hello, Nerv calling.

165
00:09:28,101 --> 00:09:31,470
Interested in info on the unknown enemy
and the appropriate countermeasures?

166
00:09:31,471 --> 00:09:34,673
This is a combat situation!
No non-essential personnel allowed!

167
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:38,343
This is just my opinion, but I'd say
this must be an Angel attack.

168
00:09:38,344 --> 00:09:40,074
All ships, fire at will!

169
00:09:40,447 --> 00:09:40,712
Roger.

170
00:09:40,713 --> 00:09:41,413
It's pointless.
Roger.

171
00:09:52,358 --> 00:09:55,287
So an AT field can't be penetrated
with this kind of firepower.

172
00:09:56,029 --> 00:09:58,199
But why is an Angel here?

173
00:09:58,965 --> 00:09:59,865
Could it be after Unit 02?

174
00:10:03,303 --> 00:10:04,763
Hey, where are we going?

175
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:08,743
Just wait here a second.

176
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,280
What's going on?

177
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:20,352
Don't peep, you pervert!

178
00:10:20,353 --> 00:10:21,353
Sorry!
