180
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,918
Why are all boys such perverted jerks?

181
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,653
Here we go, Asuka.

182
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:43,242
Why won't it sink?!

183
00:10:43,243 --> 00:10:45,353
I knew it. Only an Eva can beat it!

184
00:10:51,451 --> 00:10:52,911
Come on, let's go.

185
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:55,887
You're coming with me!

186
00:10:58,558 --> 00:11:02,094
Hey, why'd we change into these plug suits?

187
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:03,462
What are you, stupid?

188
00:11:03,463 --> 00:11:06,073
What else? We're going to beat it
with my Unit 02!

189
00:11:08,201 --> 00:11:11,236
No way! Do you have permission
from Miss Misato?

190
00:11:11,237 --> 00:11:12,906
I can get permission after I've beaten it.

191
00:11:15,909 --> 00:11:19,449
Now, I'll show you how magnificent
my piloting is, up close and personal!

192
00:11:20,713 --> 00:11:22,492
Just don't disturb me.

193
00:11:28,154 --> 00:11:30,494
This is odd. It almost seems to be
looking for something.

194
00:11:32,158 --> 00:11:34,393
For an Angel to attack here...

195
00:11:34,394 --> 00:11:36,261
Isn't it a little different from the deal we had?

196
00:11:36,262 --> 00:11:38,230
This is what Unit 02 is for,

197
00:11:38,231 --> 00:11:40,191
and I've generously provided
a second pilot as a reserve.

198
00:11:41,568 --> 00:11:44,788
If worse comes to worst, escape by yourself.

199
00:11:46,206 --> 00:11:47,196
I know.

200
00:11:50,076 --> 00:11:52,277
LCL Fullung.

201
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:54,479
Anfang der Bewegung.

202
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:57,249
Anfang des Nervenanschlusses.

203
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,770
Auslosung von Linkskleigung.

204
00:12:00,486 --> 00:12:01,686
Synchro-start.

205
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:07,593
Program error? What happened?

206
00:12:07,594 --> 00:12:10,762
Thought noise! I told you not to disturb me.

207
00:12:10,763 --> 00:12:11,830
What do you mean?

208
00:12:11,831 --> 00:12:16,235
You're thinking in Japanese, aren't you?
Think in German.

209
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:19,838
Oh, okay. Baumkuchen...

210
00:12:19,839 --> 00:12:24,639
Idiot! Just forget it.
Switch the base language to Japanese.

211
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:30,450
Evangelion Unit 02, activate.

212
00:12:31,484 --> 00:12:34,419
Telex from the Othello! Unit 02 is in
the process of activation.

213
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,454
What the...

214
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:36,625
Nice going, Asukal

215
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:41,742
No! Abort the activation sequence!
Reset it!

216
00:12:42,996 --> 00:12:44,963
Don't worry about him, Asuka! Just launch!

217
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:46,431
What are you saying?!

218
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:50,369
You can't just violate my command authority
over the Eva and its pilot!

219
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:52,204
What are you talking about?
This is an emergency!

220
00:12:52,205 --> 00:12:53,905
Who gives a damn about your procedures?

221
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:56,408
Are you really serious?

222
00:12:56,409 --> 00:12:58,839
Unit 02 is still using type B equipment!

223
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,947
Wouldn't it be bad if we fell in the sea?

224
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:03,448
So we don't fall in.

225
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:05,117
Shinji, are you in there too?

226
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:05,917
Yes.

227
00:13:05,918 --> 00:13:07,519
Two kids!

228
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,288
Good chance to test it...

229
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:10,429
Asuka, launch!

230
00:13:13,192 --> 00:13:14,159
It's coming!

231
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:14,949
Here we go!

232
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:23,435
Where is it?

233
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:23,669
That way!
Where is it?

234
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:24,540
That way!

235
00:13:25,672 --> 00:13:27,339
We've only got 58 seconds left!

236
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:29,207
I know that! Misato!

237
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:31,377
Get the external power supply onto the deck.

238
00:13:32,578 --> 00:13:33,578
Understood.

239
00:13:33,579 --> 00:13:34,913
What is she going to do?

240
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:36,415
Okay, we're going to jump!

241
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:37,266
Jump?

242
00:13:41,754 --> 00:13:42,714
Runl!

243
00:13:55,468 --> 00:13:57,002
The reserve power supply is in place!

244
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,937
Reactor connection completed!

245
00:13:58,938 --> 00:14:00,205
Evacuate the flight deck!

246
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:01,576
The deck is ready for Eva landing!

247
00:14:02,308 --> 00:14:04,176
All hands, prepare for impact!

248
00:14:04,177 --> 00:14:05,010
I can't believe this!

249
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:07,290
Eva 02, landing on deck!

250
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,157
What a waste!

251
00:14:19,158 --> 00:14:21,118
Target is approaching rapidly!

252
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:23,895
It's coming! Port, 9 o'clock!

253
00:14:23,896 --> 00:14:25,205
Switching to external power!

254
00:14:29,102 --> 00:14:30,151
Switch completed.

255
00:14:31,804 --> 00:14:33,105
But we don't have any weapons.

256
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:34,476
The prog knife will be more than enough.

257
00:14:43,516 --> 00:14:44,750
It's pretty big.

258
00:14:44,751 --> 00:14:45,771
That's what I figured!

259
00:14:48,321 --> 00:14:49,621
What are they going to do?!

260
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:52,141
Hand-to-hand combat is the best way
to defeat Angels.

261
00:15:05,538 --> 00:15:07,105
Good work stopping it, Asuka!

262
00:15:07,106 --> 00:15:09,886
That's not funny! The flight deck is a mess!

263
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:18,950
Hey, they felll

264
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:19,851
Asuka!

265
00:15:19,852 --> 00:15:22,042
It's impossible to fight underwater
with the type-B equipment!

266
00:15:22,622 --> 00:15:25,232
You never know unless you try!

267
00:15:44,143 --> 00:15:46,044
What a waste!

268
00:15:46,045 --> 00:15:47,185
How much cable is left?

269
00:15:48,648 --> 00:15:50,282
Another 1,200 meters!

270
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:51,243
What are you going to do?

271
00:15:51,851 --> 00:15:52,961
We'll manage somehow.

272
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:54,925
I've got to do something.

273
00:15:59,192 --> 00:16:01,622
The cable's going to run out!
Brace for the shock!

274
00:16:07,767 --> 00:16:08,834
Shoot!

275
00:16:08,835 --> 00:16:10,569
Eva lost the target!

276
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:12,350
Now's the time to change disks...

277
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:16,308
A Yak 38 Custom!

278
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:18,243
Hey, Katsuragi!

279
00:16:18,244 --> 00:16:19,234
Kaji!

280
00:16:20,179 --> 00:16:22,488
I've got something to deliver,
so I'll be taking off now.

281
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:25,667
Launch!

282
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:29,096
Take care of the rest of this,
Captain Katsuragi.

283
00:16:31,524 --> 00:16:33,091
He ran away.

284
00:16:33,092 --> 00:16:34,992
The target is approaching Eva again!

285
00:16:36,295 --> 00:16:37,084
It's coming again!

286
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,396
I'l finish it off this time.

287
00:16:43,436 --> 00:16:45,704
What?! It's not working!

288
00:16:45,705 --> 00:16:47,138
That's because this is B-type equipment.

289
00:16:47,139 --> 00:16:48,807
What're you going to do?!

290
00:16:48,808 --> 00:16:49,808
What am I supposed to do?

291
00:16:49,809 --> 00:16:52,329
You're pretty pitiful for being the Third Child!

292
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:53,795
Here it comes!

293
00:16:58,251 --> 00:16:59,951
A mouth?!

294
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:01,242
Well, it is an Angel.

295
00:17:04,223 --> 00:17:06,242
Eva 02 has entered the target's body.

296
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,696
Doesn't that mean they've been eaten?

297
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:12,776
It's practically like we're fishing!

298
00:17:13,398 --> 00:17:15,648
Fishing? Yes, fishing!

299
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:19,938
We're right back in a pinch now.

300
00:17:19,939 --> 00:17:21,049
Shut up!

301
00:17:22,108 --> 00:17:24,509
Hey, get off me already, you pervert!

302
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:26,545
But we've got to free ourselves somehow.

303
00:17:26,546 --> 00:17:28,146
Asuka, do you read me?

304
00:17:28,146 --> 00:17:29,667
Don't let go, no matter what!

305
00:17:31,284 --> 00:17:32,250
Captain...

306
00:17:32,251 --> 00:17:33,041
What?

307
00:17:33,553 --> 00:17:35,103
I'm requesting your cooperation.

308
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:40,062
A point-blank assault by two
of the surviving battleships?!

309
00:17:40,693 --> 00:17:41,660
Correct.

310
00:17:41,661 --> 00:17:46,291
We'll scuttle two of the evacuated battleships
along the umbilical cable and set a trap.

311
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:51,069
During that time, Eva 02 will open
the target's mouth,

312
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,871
both ships will rush in,

313
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:55,574
fire all of their bow turret cannons,

314
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:58,035
and then self-destruct, destroying the target.

315
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,021
That's absurd!

316
00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:03,143
Absurd, perhaps, but I don't think
it's impossible.

317
00:18:04,717 --> 00:18:05,784
I understand.

318
00:18:05,785 --> 00:18:08,625
All hands, abandon ship!
Repeat, all hands, abandon ship!

319
00:18:09,522 --> 00:18:11,802
All frigates, hurry and rescue the lifeboats!

320
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:14,385
But what about the Eva?

321
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:17,562
Not to worry. They'll be fine.

322
00:18:17,563 --> 00:18:20,663
Hey! Don't use Unit 02
without my permission!

323
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:24,069
Do the two of you understand the operation?

324
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,570
I'll do my best.

325
00:18:25,571 --> 00:18:26,501
I'm counting on you.

326
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:34,379
Both ships have opened the Kingston valve!
Scuttling towards point Z.

327
00:18:34,380 --> 00:18:35,413
Roger!

328
00:18:35,414 --> 00:18:36,614
Cable reverse!

329
00:18:44,390 --> 00:18:45,657
Eva has started to surface!

330
00:18:45,658 --> 00:18:46,947
T-minus 70 to contact!

331
00:18:49,095 --> 00:18:52,297
Hey, how long are you going to stay there?
Get off me already!

332
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:55,288
But we've got to pry open its mouth soon,
or we'll be killed too!

333
00:18:59,338 --> 00:19:01,039
T-minus 60 to contact.

334
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,007
Status on the Angel's mouth?

335
00:19:02,008 --> 00:19:02,240
It's still not open!
Status on the Angel's mouth?

336
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:02,851
It's still not open!

337
00:19:05,611 --> 00:19:08,580
Both battleships are sinking
towards the target.

338
00:19:08,581 --> 00:19:11,149
Eva is continuing to surface,
T-minus 50 to contact.

339
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:12,017
It's not working!

340
00:19:12,018 --> 00:19:13,188
There's no time left!

341
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:21,426
Target has passed beneath the Tempest!

342
00:19:21,427 --> 00:19:22,694
Speed of ascent increasing!

343
00:19:22,695 --> 00:19:23,925
You're not going to make it! Hurry!

344
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:26,398
Don't get any strange ideas.

345
00:19:26,399 --> 00:19:27,265
About what?

346
00:19:27,266 --> 00:19:29,734
Anyway, just focus your thoughts.

347
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:30,635
I know!

348
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:37,438
T-minus 20 to contact!

349
00:19:40,379 --> 00:19:42,049
T-minus 15 to contact!

350
00:19:42,515 --> 00:19:44,245
Open! Open! Open! Open!

351
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,550
Open! Open! Open! Open!

352
00:19:58,497 --> 00:19:59,547
Fire!

353
00:20:17,316 --> 00:20:20,336
New Yokosuka (Old Odawara)

354
00:20:22,088 --> 00:20:23,822
You certainly went all-out.

355
00:20:23,823 --> 00:20:26,603
I should have anticipated
underwater combat.

356
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:29,761
Oh, how rare. Remorse?

357
00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:33,364
Who cares? We collected valuable data too.

358
00:20:33,365 --> 00:20:34,325
That's true.

359
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:36,236
Misato...

360
00:20:37,369 --> 00:20:38,769
This really is something special.

361
00:20:45,878 --> 00:20:47,312
They MATCH!

362
00:20:47,313 --> 00:20:48,833
I don't believe this!

363
00:20:49,381 --> 00:20:51,716
They broke their synchronization
ratio records, didn't they?

364
00:20:51,717 --> 00:20:54,407
For only seven seconds.
It must have been due to the danger.

365
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,889
Hey, where's Mr. Kaji?

366
00:20:57,890 --> 00:21:01,320
He ran off. That idiot's got to be back
at headquarters by now!

367
00:21:03,329 --> 00:21:05,959
It was a pretty eventful trip.

368
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,708
Was it caused by this, after all?

369
00:21:13,739 --> 00:21:16,341
It's already restored itself this far.

370
00:21:16,342 --> 00:21:19,912
It's frozen inside dura-bakelite,
but it's still alive.

371
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:24,549
Without a doubt, this is the keystone of the
Human Instrumentality Project, isn't it?

372
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:25,550
Correct.

373
00:21:25,551 --> 00:21:27,652
This is the first human being.

374
00:21:27,653 --> 00:21:28,443
Adam.

375
00:21:29,822 --> 00:21:34,492
She may have looked cute,
but she was a real bitch.

376
00:21:34,493 --> 00:21:37,462
Well, we won't have to see her again.

377
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:40,165
Yeah, though ol' Mister Big Shot
has to see her at work.

378
00:21:40,166 --> 00:21:41,505
Man, I feel sorry for ya.

379
00:21:55,514 --> 00:21:58,444
My name is Asuka Langley Sohryu.
Nice to meet you.

380
00:21:58,918 --> 00:22:00,618
To Be Continued

381
00:23:06,318 --> 00:23:07,108
Preview

382
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:10,088
Asuka and Shinji, who are on completely
different wavelengths,

383
00:23:10,089 --> 00:23:12,257
are soundly beaten by an Angel.

384
00:23:12,258 --> 00:23:15,927
Aiming for perfect unison between the two,
Misato comes up with a plan.

